<subSubSection id="C30043C2A53265450DEFF779FA9FF839" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA51049A53265450DEFF779FA9FF839" blockId="0.[151,1437,1475,2005]" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">
<emphasis id="B96ECC5BA53265450DEFF779FE98F9A5" box="[199,316,1585,1609]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B96ECC5BA53265450DEFF779FE91F9A5" bold="true" box="[199,309,1585,1609]" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Externally, the new species (
<figureCitation id="13210CCCA53265450F55F779FD19F9A5" box="[637,701,1585,1609]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[165,1435,185,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-28@1.[152,1436,182,1930]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Epimecia (1–3) and Lophoterges (4–8) spp.: adults. Depositories of specimens: 1, 2, 5–8—BBT; 3—STP; 4—AFM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406514/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) differs clearly from 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A6BCAA53265450E84F77AFBA9F9A5" baseAuthorityName="Freyer" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[940,1037,1585,1609]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Epimecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ustula">
<emphasis id="B96ECC5BA53265450E84F77AFBA9F9A5" box="[940,1037,1585,1609]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">E. ustula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13210CCCA53265450936F779FBDBF9A5" box="[1054,1151,1585,1609]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[165,1435,185,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-28@1.[152,1436,182,1930]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Epimecia (1–3) and Lophoterges (4–8) spp.: adults. Depositories of specimens: 1, 2, 5–8—BBT; 3—STP; 4—AFM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406514/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Figs 2, 3</figureCitation>
) by its remarkably different forewing pattern resembling that of members of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A6BCAA53265450E12F71DFC1AF981" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1906" box="[826,958,1621,1645]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoterges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96ECC5BA53265450E12F71DFC1AF981" box="[826,958,1621,1645]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Lophoterges</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13210CCCA53265450EE5F71DFB94F981" box="[973,1072,1621,1645]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[165,1435,185,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-28@1.[152,1436,182,1930]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Epimecia (1–3) and Lophoterges (4–8) spp.: adults. Depositories of specimens: 1, 2, 5–8—BBT; 3—STP; 4—AFM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406514/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Figs 4–8</figureCitation>
). It is most similar to the Chinese (Qinghai, Kuku Nor (
<typeStatus id="54A1AEEBA53265450C55F731FE08F97D" box="[381,428,1657,1681]" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">type</typeStatus>
locality) and Gansu, Xiahe) 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A6BCAA53265450FC8F732FC90F97D" baseAuthorityName="Pungeler" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[736,820,1657,1681]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoterges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fatua">
<emphasis id="B96ECC5BA53265450FC8F732FC90F97D" box="[736,820,1657,1681]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">L. fatua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13210CCCA53265450E6AF731FC20F97D" box="[834,900,1657,1681]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[165,1435,185,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-28@1.[152,1436,182,1930]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Epimecia (1–3) and Lophoterges (4–8) spp.: adults. Depositories of specimens: 1, 2, 5–8—BBT; 3—STP; 4—AFM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406514" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406514/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), but differs by its smaller size, ash-grey forewing ground colour (that is brownish in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A6BCAA53265450F3CF7D6FDCDF959" baseAuthorityName="Pungeler" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[532,617,1693,1717]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoterges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fatua">
<emphasis id="B96ECC5BA53265450F3CF7D6FDCDF959" box="[532,617,1693,1717]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">L. fatua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the configuration and colouration of the reniform and orbicular spots. Compared to the three other 
<taxonomicName id="4C1A6BCAA53265450CE0F789FDE8F935" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1906" box="[456,588,1729,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoterges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96ECC5BA53265450CE0F789FDE8F935" box="[456,588,1729,1753]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Lophoterges</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species occurring in 
<collectingCountry id="F30D50D9A53265450E06F789FC0EF935" box="[814,938,1729,1753]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="0" pageNumber="288">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C1A6BCAA53265450E92F789FA3CF935" authority="(Staudinger, 1901)" baseAuthorityName="Staudinger" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[954,1432,1729,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Lophoterges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="288" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="centralasiae">
